&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Just for fun I tried a more *generic* solution.

The problem with `scale` seems to be that it doesn&#39;t *re renders* other objects position. But if you change the actual *width* and *height*, it works.

But that adds another problem, you need to add in your CSS the initial width and height for the *transition* to work.

What I did was use [CSS variables](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Using_CSS_custom_properties). You need to specify the dimensions of each image, but that makes the CSS reusable, it will work with variable image dimensions.

But if all your images have the same dimensions, you could just add those values directly to the CSS file and avoid using CSS variables.

With [calc()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/calc) I multiplied the initial width by 1.25 (which is the same as 25%).

**Edit: removed height because it&#39;s not necessary**

View the examples in full page.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .item img {
      width: var(--w); /* 320px */
      height: auto;
      transition: all 0.5s ease;
    }

    .item img:hover,
    .item img:active {
      width: calc(var(--w) * 1.25); /* calc(320px * 1.25) */
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;container item&quot;&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;
        &lt;img src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/output/nature-q-c-320-240-8.jpg&quot; style=&quot;--w:320px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h4&gt;Name&lt;/h4&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum...&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container item&quot;&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;
        &lt;img src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/output/nature-q-c-640-480-8.jpg&quot; style=&quot;--w:640px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h4&gt;Name&lt;/h4&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum...&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Responsive example:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

