answers.body_markdown:
The problem is  the class **.view-first .mask**.

For the expected result the class mentioned needs POSITION: ABSOLUTE and not RELATIVE.

```
.view-first .mask  {
 position: absolute;
 display: block;
 opacity: 0;
 background-color: rgba(255,0,4,0.57);
 transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out;
 height: 100%; 
}
```

Doing so will achieve the expected result, but another problem will appear. You will need to adjust the margin-top of the following classes:

**.view-first p**

**.view a.info**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .view-first .mask  {
      position: relative;
      display: block;
      opacity: 0;
      /* background-color: rgba(255,0,4,0.57); */
      transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out;
      height: 100%; 
    }

    .view.view-first {
      transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out;
    }

    .view.view-first:hover {
      background: rgba(255,0,4,0.57);
      transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out;
    }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Remove `background-color: rgba(255,0,4,0.57);` from `.view-first .mask` div and give it to the parent div so the whole div will get the color

